
--- Lessons Learned ---


• Self reflect and improve the incident response process

• Post-Incident Reviews
  → Postmortem reports
  → Who, what, where, why, how?

• Lessons Learned Meetings
  → When was the problem first detected?
  → Who detected it?
  → What was the scope of the incident?
  → How was it contained, eradicated, and recovered?
  → How were we effective?
  → What are areas for improvement?
  → Questions, suggestions, and discussions



References
